A cyclist, believed to be in his 40s, is in a critical condition after he was knocked over by a motorcycle on the corner of Rondebult and Ravenswood roads in Boksburg in Ekurhuleni on Saturday morning, paramedics said.
ER24 paramedics arrived at the scene at about 6.50am and found the man lying in the road, ER24 spokeswoman Annine Siddall said.
The patient was treated and transported to a nearby hospital for further medical care. The cause of the accident was unknown at this stage, she said.